<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="950" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d950">
                        <head><hi rend="italic"><gloss type="from">Nicaraguan Minister of Foreign
                                    Affairs</gloss> to <gloss type="to">Secretary of Chilean
                                    Legation, Washington</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-07"><hi rend="italic">August 7,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I beg of you to communicate to the Secretary of State that the Government
                            has ordered the return of the duties to the American merchants.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Corea.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>